<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REMOVE - OUTPUT SHAFT AND REAR BEARING ASSEMBLIES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OUTPUT SHAFT AND REAR BEARING ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the output shaft forward and through the rear bearing
                assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301956">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301956" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301956" filename="../figg13/G1301956.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Drive Output Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing retaining bolts, rear bearing cover, and gasket from the auxiliary
                housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301957">Figure 57</hotlnk>). The rear bearing cone drops from the housing bore when
                the cover is removed. If necessary, remove the oil seal from the cover (inset).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301957" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301957" filename="../figg13/G1301957.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Remove Retaining Bolts, Rear Bearing Cover, and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two bearing cups and spacer from the bearing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301958">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1301958" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301958" filename="../figg13/G1301958.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 58. Remove Bearing Cups and Spacer From Bearing Bore</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
